<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
Medium sized (7.7-11.2 mm), with olive-brown reflection; antennae reddish brown; body pile predominantly pale, except some black pile on vertex and terga 2-4 medially; basoflagellomere short, ca. 1.2 times as long as wide, with large dorsal to dorsolateral fossette, and short arista (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figure 19. Antenna. A Merodon hirsutus, outer side, lateral view, male B Merodon hirsutus, inner side, lateral view, male C Merodon hirsutus, dorsal view, male D Merodon hirsutus, outer side, lateral view, female E Merodon kawamurae, outer side, lateral view, male F Merodon kawamurae, inner side, lateral view, male G Merodon kawamurae, dorsal view, male H Merodon kawamurae, outer side, lateral view, female I Merodon medium sp. nov., outer side, lateral view, male J Merodon medium sp. nov., outer side, lateral view, female. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.909.46838.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/377380" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">19E-H</figureCitation>
); tergum 2 with reddish yellow lateral maculae; tergum 3 laterally reddish or brown; metafemur incrassate with long pilosity as long as half of width of metafemur in male and as one third of width of metafemur in female (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F22" captionText="Figure 22. A, B metaleg, C, D metatrochanter, metafemur and metatibia, lateral view. A Merodon kawamurae, male B Merodon kawamurae, female C Merodon medium sp. nov., male D Merodon medium sp. nov., female. Scale bar: 2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.909.46838.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/377383" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">22A, B</figureCitation>
); male genitalia: posterior surstyle lobe with small lateral hump (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Male genitalia. A Merodon disjunctus sp. nov., epandrium, lateral view B Merodon disjunctus sp. nov., epandrium, ventral view C Merodon disjunctus sp. nov., hypandrium, lateral view D Merodon kawamurae, epandrium, lateral view E Merodon kawamurae, epandrium, ventral view F Merodon kawamurae, hypandrium, lateral view. Abbreviations: al-anterior surstyle lobe, bp-basolateral protrusion, l-lingula, pl-posterior surstyle lobe, s-lateral sclerite of aedeagus. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.909.46838.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/377379" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">18E</figureCitation>
: bp); apical part of anterior surstyle lobe rhomboid (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Male genitalia. A Merodon disjunctus sp. nov., epandrium, lateral view B Merodon disjunctus sp. nov., epandrium, ventral view C Merodon disjunctus sp. nov., hypandrium, lateral view D Merodon kawamurae, epandrium, lateral view E Merodon kawamurae, epandrium, ventral view F Merodon kawamurae, hypandrium, lateral view. Abbreviations: al-anterior surstyle lobe, bp-basolateral protrusion, l-lingula, pl-posterior surstyle lobe, s-lateral sclerite of aedeagus. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.909.46838.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/377379" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">18D</figureCitation>
: al); lingula large (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Male genitalia. A Merodon disjunctus sp. nov., epandrium, lateral view B Merodon disjunctus sp. nov., epandrium, ventral view C Merodon disjunctus sp. nov., hypandrium, lateral view D Merodon kawamurae, epandrium, lateral view E Merodon kawamurae, epandrium, ventral view F Merodon kawamurae, hypandrium, lateral view. Abbreviations: al-anterior surstyle lobe, bp-basolateral protrusion, l-lingula, pl-posterior surstyle lobe, s-lateral sclerite of aedeagus. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.909.46838.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/377379" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">18F</figureCitation>
: l), lateral sclerite of aedeagus elongated (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Male genitalia. A Merodon disjunctus sp. nov., epandrium, lateral view B Merodon disjunctus sp. nov., epandrium, ventral view C Merodon disjunctus sp. nov., hypandrium, lateral view D Merodon kawamurae, epandrium, lateral view E Merodon kawamurae, epandrium, ventral view F Merodon kawamurae, hypandrium, lateral view. Abbreviations: al-anterior surstyle lobe, bp-basolateral protrusion, l-lingula, pl-posterior surstyle lobe, s-lateral sclerite of aedeagus. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.909.46838.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/377379" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">18F</figureCitation>
: s).
</paragraph>
