<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
Male genitalia. Apical part of anterior surstyle lobe rhomboid shape, covered with dense, short pile (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Male genitalia. A Merodon disjunctus sp. nov., epandrium, lateral view B Merodon disjunctus sp. nov., epandrium, ventral view C Merodon disjunctus sp. nov., hypandrium, lateral view D Merodon kawamurae, epandrium, lateral view E Merodon kawamurae, epandrium, ventral view F Merodon kawamurae, hypandrium, lateral view. Abbreviations: al-anterior surstyle lobe, bp-basolateral protrusion, l-lingula, pl-posterior surstyle lobe, s-lateral sclerite of aedeagus. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.909.46838.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/377379" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">18D</figureCitation>
: al); posterior surstyle lobe oval with small basolateral protrusion (lateral hump) (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Male genitalia. A Merodon disjunctus sp. nov., epandrium, lateral view B Merodon disjunctus sp. nov., epandrium, ventral view C Merodon disjunctus sp. nov., hypandrium, lateral view D Merodon kawamurae, epandrium, lateral view E Merodon kawamurae, epandrium, ventral view F Merodon kawamurae, hypandrium, lateral view. Abbreviations: al-anterior surstyle lobe, bp-basolateral protrusion, l-lingula, pl-posterior surstyle lobe, s-lateral sclerite of aedeagus. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.909.46838.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/377379" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">18E</figureCitation>
: bp); hypandrium sickle-shaped, without lateral projections; lingula large (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Male genitalia. A Merodon disjunctus sp. nov., epandrium, lateral view B Merodon disjunctus sp. nov., epandrium, ventral view C Merodon disjunctus sp. nov., hypandrium, lateral view D Merodon kawamurae, epandrium, lateral view E Merodon kawamurae, epandrium, ventral view F Merodon kawamurae, hypandrium, lateral view. Abbreviations: al-anterior surstyle lobe, bp-basolateral protrusion, l-lingula, pl-posterior surstyle lobe, s-lateral sclerite of aedeagus. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.909.46838.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/377379" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">18F</figureCitation>
: l); lateral sclerite of aedeagus elongated (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Male genitalia. A Merodon disjunctus sp. nov., epandrium, lateral view B Merodon disjunctus sp. nov., epandrium, ventral view C Merodon disjunctus sp. nov., hypandrium, lateral view D Merodon kawamurae, epandrium, lateral view E Merodon kawamurae, epandrium, ventral view F Merodon kawamurae, hypandrium, lateral view. Abbreviations: al-anterior surstyle lobe, bp-basolateral protrusion, l-lingula, pl-posterior surstyle lobe, s-lateral sclerite of aedeagus. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.909.46838.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/377379" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">18F</figureCitation>
: s).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Female.</emphasis>
Similar to the male except for normal sexual dimorphism and for the following characteristics: antennae with rounded tip, fossette dorsolateral (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 19" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figure 19. Antenna. A Merodon hirsutus, outer side, lateral view, male B Merodon hirsutus, inner side, lateral view, male C Merodon hirsutus, dorsal view, male D Merodon hirsutus, outer side, lateral view, female E Merodon kawamurae, outer side, lateral view, male F Merodon kawamurae, inner side, lateral view, male G Merodon kawamurae, dorsal view, male H Merodon kawamurae, outer side, lateral view, female I Merodon medium sp. nov., outer side, lateral view, male J Merodon medium sp. nov., outer side, lateral view, female. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.909.46838.figure19" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/377380" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">19D</figureCitation>
); frons microtrichose, covered with mostly gray-yellow pile; ocellar triangle covered with black pile; long pile on postero- and anteroventral surface ca. as half of width of metafemur (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F22" captionText="Figure 22. A, B metaleg, C, D metatrochanter, metafemur and metatibia, lateral view. A Merodon kawamurae, male B Merodon kawamurae, female C Merodon medium sp. nov., male D Merodon medium sp. nov., female. Scale bar: 2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.909.46838.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/377383" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">22B</figureCitation>
); microtrichose fasciae on terga 2-4 narrower (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 23" captionStartId="F23" captionText="Figure 23. Body parts, dorsal view. A Merodon trianguloculus sp. nov., thorax, male B Merodon trianguloculus sp. nov., thorax, female C Merodon trianguloculus sp. nov., abdomen, male D Merodon trianguloculus sp. nov., abdomen, female E Merodon kawamurae, abdomen, male F Merodon kawamurae, abdomen, female. Scale bar: 2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.909.46838.figure23" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/377384" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">23F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
